      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T07:20:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the question. `exposed_by` / `exposing` follows the\nexisting PDI convention used between PCIeFunction and PCIeDevice\n[1][2]: a logical function and the physical device that exposes\nit.\n\nSome context on the related verbs:\n\n- `produced_by` / `producing`: the producer creates the function\n  (e.g., a PCIe function produces this network function).\n- `contained_by` / `containing`: physical containment (e.g., a\n  chassis containing items).\n- `exposed_by` / `exposing`: a physical device exposes a logical\n  function -- the case we have here for NetworkAdapter and\n  NetworkInterface.\n\nPlease let me know if a different verb is preferred and I will\nupdate accordingly. Thanks.\n\n[1] yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item/PCIeFunction.interface.yaml\n[2] yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item/PCIeDevice.interface.yaml",
      "parentUuid": "453dd306_d3465b6e",
      "revId": "79106fd0f7c4f11bab836c319ea0aed36112e4bf",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
