      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the pointer. Renamed in PS3 to follow requirements.md:\n\n- `assignable_physical_network_ports` -\u003e `assigned_to`\n- `assigned_network_device_function` -\u003e `assigning`\n\nSentence test:\n- NetworkInterface is `assigned_to` the Port.\n- Port is `assigning` the NetworkInterface.\n\nFor context, the existing `connecting` / `connected_to` uses in\nPDI describe physical hardware connections (FabricAdapter,\nNetworkAdapter, Cpu, Cable, PCIeSwitch, etc.). Since\nNetworkInterface is a logical MAC/function rather than a physical\nentity, a new participle pair seemed clearer than reusing\n`connecting` here.\n\nPlease let me know if different naming is preferred and I will\nupdate accordingly. Thanks.",
